Step 1 :  create a project folder 
mkdir node-task-api 
cd node-task-api 

Step 2: initialize Node.js 
npm init -y   # this will create package.json 

Step 3: Install Dependencies 
npm install express cors 

Step 4: Create the APP file 
touch index.js

nano index.js and copy the file into it 

before you save you can change the port number if port 3000 is not available 

Ctrl o enter Ctrl x to save and exit 

Step 5:  Test it Locally first

node index.js  # Start the server 

Step 6: 
access node-task-api via http://<ubuntu_ip>:3000/tasks 

Step 7:  Quick API test with curl 

curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/tasks \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
-d '{"title": "Node API testing", "done": false}'

Once this works locally then we can now Dockerize the Node.js Express API 






